WEBVTT

00:02.436 --> 00:03.969
           NARRATOR:
       <i> Once upon a time,</i>

00:04.005 --> 00:07.072
      <i> in a mythical place</i>
     <i> called Cape Kennedy,</i>

00:07.108 --> 00:10.809
<i> an astronaut named Tony Nelson</i>
  <i> went up on a space mission.</i>

00:10.845 --> 00:12.277
     <i> The missile went up,</i>

00:12.312 --> 00:15.780
   <i> but something went wrong,</i>
<i> and they had to bring it down.</i>

00:15.816 --> 00:20.385
   <i> Captain Nelson landed on</i>
<i>an island in the South Pacific,</i>

00:20.420 --> 00:22.087
   <i> where he found a bottle.</i>

00:22.122 --> 00:23.721
           <i> At least,</i>
   <i> it looked like a bottle.</i>

00:23.757 --> 00:25.790
       <i> But it didn't act</i>
        <i> like a bottle.</i>

00:25.826 --> 00:27.292
             [♪♪♪]

00:27.328 --> 00:29.828
  <i> Because in it was a genie.</i>

00:29.864 --> 00:32.397
     <i> Oh, not your average</i>
        <i> everyday genie,</i>

00:32.432 --> 00:34.432
   <i> but a beautiful genie...</i>

00:35.468 --> 00:37.969
 <i> ...who could grant</i> any <i> wish.</i>

00:38.004 --> 00:39.871
             [♪♪♪]

01:02.696 --> 01:05.997
<i>Captain Nelson was so grateful,</i>
     <i> he set Jeannie free,</i>

01:06.033 --> 01:07.432
     <i> only she didn't want</i>
          <i> to be free.</i>

01:07.468 --> 01:09.034
      <i> You know how it is</i>

01:09.069 --> 01:12.437
  <i> when you've been cooped up</i>
  <i> in a bottle for 2000 years.</i>

01:12.473 --> 01:14.039
    <i> She wanted to have fun.</i>

01:14.074 --> 01:16.875
   <i> And she wanted to have it</i>
     <i> with Captain Nelson.</i>

01:16.910 --> 01:19.478
   <i> So she followed him back</i>
        <i> to Cocoa Beach,</i>

01:19.513 --> 01:20.612
        <i> a mythical town</i>

01:20.648 --> 01:23.582
      <i> in a mythical state</i>
        <i> called Florida.</i>

01:23.617 --> 01:24.916
   <i> And there in this house,</i>

01:24.951 --> 01:28.220
    <i> the girl in the bottle</i>
   <i> plays Spin the Astronaut.</i>

01:28.255 --> 01:30.855
             [♪♪♪]

01:55.382 --> 01:56.348
           Good morning, master.

01:56.383 --> 01:57.349
Good morning, Jeannie.

01:57.384 --> 01:58.350
  You hungry?

01:58.385 --> 01:59.384
                      Mm, yes.

01:59.420 --> 02:01.619
    Help yourself
to anything you'd like.

02:01.655 --> 02:03.422
                  [GIGGLES]

02:03.457 --> 02:05.924
  I-- I'm not on the menu.

02:05.959 --> 02:07.225
      Try the sausage,
            huh?

02:07.261 --> 02:08.626
                    [SIGHS]

02:08.662 --> 02:10.828
Hey, wait a minute. We got
an emergency meeting call

02:10.864 --> 02:11.996
       this morning.

02:12.032 --> 02:14.499
Oh, boy, I'm going to be late.
          Excuse me.

02:19.873 --> 02:22.440
Thou art always away slaving.

02:22.476 --> 02:24.242
                     Mm.
             Say, tell you what.

02:24.277 --> 02:26.177
       Tonight, when it's really
             good and dark,

02:26.213 --> 02:28.413
       why don't I take you
  for a long drive on the beach.

02:28.448 --> 02:29.414
                How about that?

02:29.449 --> 02:32.383
  That sounds wonderful.

02:32.419 --> 02:34.252
  What shall I do all day?

02:34.287 --> 02:35.854
          Mm, well, you'll think
              of something.

02:35.889 --> 02:38.657
             Goodbye, Jeannie.
           I'll see you tonight.

02:40.260 --> 02:42.227
                Jeannie...

02:42.696 --> 02:44.329
      [SIGHS]

02:52.606 --> 02:54.172
      Jeannie, stop that.

03:07.153 --> 03:08.653
             [♪♪♪]

03:13.727 --> 03:15.226
             [♪♪♪]

03:18.264 --> 03:20.164
 Because of the very nature
      of this mission,

03:20.200 --> 03:23.301
we're not going to force anyone
   to accept this assignment.

03:23.336 --> 03:25.971
     We're asking for
       a volunteer.

03:26.006 --> 03:28.172
             [MAN CLEARS THROAT]

03:30.343 --> 03:31.910
            Carson?

03:33.514 --> 03:35.580
           Davenport?

03:36.717 --> 03:39.083
        What about you,
        Captain Healey?

03:39.119 --> 03:41.653
Colonel, I'd gladly serve above
 and beyond the call of duty,

03:41.688 --> 03:45.089
but this is even beyond
   above and beyond.

03:45.125 --> 03:49.427
Gentlemen, I don't mind telling
you I am bitterly disappointed.

03:49.462 --> 03:50.996
      Surely there must
       be one among you

03:51.031 --> 03:52.697
     willing to undertake
       this assignment.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.966
   Yeah, sir, I don't understand
      what this is all about,

03:55.002 --> 03:56.935
               but I'd like to--
Thank you, Captain Nelson.

03:56.970 --> 03:59.170
     Report immediately
to General Fletcher's office.

04:00.373 --> 04:03.474
     Uh, Fred, what's this...?
             Uh...Fred?

04:06.580 --> 04:07.979
         A guided tour?

04:08.015 --> 04:09.247
      You must be joking,
            general.

04:09.282 --> 04:11.349
       I-- I understood this
    to be an important mission.

04:11.384 --> 04:14.419
 P.J. Ferguson is the president
 of the largest aerospace firm

04:14.454 --> 04:15.687
        in the country.

04:15.722 --> 04:18.423
        He has served as
a technical consultant to NATO.

04:18.458 --> 04:19.558
                And Senator Kane

04:19.593 --> 04:21.692
           of the Armed Forces
        Appropriations Committee

04:21.728 --> 04:23.595
          is his closest friend.

04:23.630 --> 04:24.996
             Are you reading me,
                   captain?

04:25.032 --> 04:26.898
Loud and clear, sir.

04:26.934 --> 04:29.400
    Mr. Ferguson and his family
    are cruising on their yacht.

04:29.436 --> 04:31.803
            They stopped by here
               just for today.

04:31.838 --> 04:34.405
   And he specifically suggested
     a bright, young astronaut

04:34.441 --> 04:35.674
                for the tour.

04:35.709 --> 04:38.643
    You are a bright, young
astronaut, are you not, captain?

04:38.679 --> 04:39.811
I always thought I was, sir,

04:39.846 --> 04:42.447
until I volunteered
for this assignment.

04:42.482 --> 04:44.816
  The Fergusons are here,
          general.

04:44.851 --> 04:46.217
I don't intend to...

04:48.589 --> 04:49.821
go back on my word, sir.

04:49.856 --> 04:51.222
    I'll be glad
to conduct the tour.

04:51.257 --> 04:52.256
                      Good man.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.625
    P.J.
                Bill.

04:53.660 --> 04:55.060
      This is
Captain Tony Nelson.

04:55.095 --> 04:56.327
                       Captain.
How do you do, sir?

04:56.362 --> 04:58.863
       Mr. Ferguson
     and Miss Ferguson.

04:58.899 --> 05:02.200
          Captain Nelson.
   I never thought we'd get you.

05:02.235 --> 05:03.635
               It's a privilege.

05:03.670 --> 05:06.571
    No, it's my privilege...
  and an unexpected pleasure.

05:06.607 --> 05:09.040
           Been looking forward
          to this tour, captain.

05:09.075 --> 05:11.643
  Wanted to see how our latest
component parts are working out.

05:11.678 --> 05:13.511
          I'd be happy
    to show you around, sir.

05:13.547 --> 05:15.913
          Mm, not-- Not too, uh,
            technical, Father.

05:15.949 --> 05:20.418
      Remember, this is still...
           a pleasure trip.

05:23.156 --> 05:24.289
Boy, I feel guilty.

05:24.324 --> 05:26.291
I could have tipped poor Tony
    off when he came in.

05:26.326 --> 05:28.059
           It's not your fault
         he wanted to be a hero.

05:28.094 --> 05:30.328
    I know, but it's a lousy
assignment he got hung up with.

05:30.363 --> 05:31.329
             TONY:
        Mr. Ferguson...

05:31.364 --> 05:33.064
Uh, uh, watch it, guys.

05:33.099 --> 05:34.833
             [♪♪♪]

05:34.868 --> 05:37.769
        This is a group
    of the walking wounded.

05:37.805 --> 05:39.237
    Shock, you know.

05:44.344 --> 05:45.944
             [♪♪♪]

06:00.360 --> 06:03.528
This young man has real
engineering savvy, Bill.

06:03.564 --> 06:05.530
  Made some interesting
      suggestions.

06:05.565 --> 06:08.166
   Don't get any ideas, P.J.,
     we intend to keep him.

06:09.102 --> 06:10.334
Oh, I'd like you and your staff

06:10.370 --> 06:12.170
    on-board the <i> Nina</i> tonight
          for cocktails.

06:12.205 --> 06:13.538
   We're sailing in the morning.

06:13.573 --> 06:15.373
           Thank you.
    I'll pass out the word.

06:15.408 --> 06:17.876
              You will be there,
               won't you, Tony?

06:17.911 --> 06:19.343
  I'm sorry, Nina.

06:19.379 --> 06:20.344
          I've made other plans.

06:20.380 --> 06:21.646
                         NINA:
                          Oh.

06:21.681 --> 06:24.482
  Nothing that can't be changed,
            I'm sure.

06:24.518 --> 06:26.651
Well, I did promise someone
     else, sir, and--

06:26.686 --> 06:29.888
You wouldn't put pleasure
before duty, would you, captain?

06:29.923 --> 06:32.657
Especially since this duty
is such a pleasure.

06:32.692 --> 06:34.358
       Yes, sir.

06:34.394 --> 06:35.593
      I'll be there.

06:35.629 --> 06:37.328
         She'll understand.

06:37.363 --> 06:39.096
   But you don't understand!

06:43.636 --> 06:45.570
 Hey, wait a minute,
   wait a minute!

06:45.605 --> 06:47.005
     You don't understand!

06:47.040 --> 06:48.773
       Oh, I understand.

06:48.809 --> 06:50.675
    You promised to take me
     to the beach tonight,

06:50.711 --> 06:53.245
 but instead, you would rather
   go out on someone's yacht.

06:53.280 --> 06:54.445
     I was ordered to.

06:54.481 --> 06:55.914
 It's-- It's business.
                         Ha!

06:55.949 --> 06:57.015
        Then I will go with you.

06:57.050 --> 06:58.850
     I am very good at business.

06:58.885 --> 07:01.218
Oh, no, you won't.

07:01.254 --> 07:03.120
          And who is to stop me?

07:03.156 --> 07:04.756
I am.

07:04.791 --> 07:07.224
                  [LAUGHS]

07:09.863 --> 07:13.297
    Oh, come on, now.
Now, stop that, will you?

07:13.332 --> 07:15.934
Look, look, I don't have
any time to fool around.

07:15.969 --> 07:17.068
  I'm late as it is.

07:17.103 --> 07:18.369
        Jeannie,
  come on out of there.

07:18.404 --> 07:19.971
         Come--

07:20.006 --> 07:21.940
     Oh, all right,
     stay in there.

07:33.053 --> 07:34.686
         [VACUUM WHIRS]

07:36.690 --> 07:40.458
Jeannie, I'd, uh, like to
talk to you about tonight.

07:41.127 --> 07:43.160
 Now, come on.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.932
Come closer.

07:56.209 --> 07:57.775
    Sorry about this,
        Jeannie,

07:57.811 --> 08:01.947
but your old master has a little
  modern magic up his sleeve.

08:04.952 --> 08:08.653
 Now, you're gonna stay at home
   tonight, like a good girl.

08:11.325 --> 08:13.024
  [JAZZY DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

08:29.309 --> 08:30.408
             Tony!

08:30.444 --> 08:31.409
             Huh? Hi.

08:31.445 --> 08:32.477
             Oh, sorry.

08:32.511 --> 08:34.044
Captain Roger Healey,
    this is Nina.

08:34.081 --> 08:35.780
                    Wow.
            If you're the <i> Nina,</i>

08:35.815 --> 08:38.249
I'd love to see what the <i> Pinta </i>
 and the <i> Santa Maria</i> look like.

08:38.284 --> 08:40.318
   And that, Captain Healey,
      calls for champagne.

08:40.354 --> 08:41.318
           Follow me.

08:41.355 --> 08:43.054
       To the ends of the Earth.

08:44.358 --> 08:45.490
           Oh, I'm sorry.

08:45.525 --> 08:46.825
                     Sorry,
                you're sorry...?

08:46.860 --> 08:48.559
          [WHISTLING]

09:00.073 --> 09:01.772
[CLEARS THROAT]

09:01.808 --> 09:03.574
Captain Roger Healey,
     U.S. Army.

09:03.609 --> 09:05.776
Of course, you know that
if you read the newspapers.

09:05.812 --> 09:08.913
What's it like orbiting the
Earth at 18,000 miles an hour?

09:08.949 --> 09:09.981
Exhilarating.

09:10.016 --> 09:11.382
The freedom
of weightlessness,

09:11.417 --> 09:14.418
the color of the sunrise
and the sunsets...

09:14.454 --> 09:15.619
                   Please go on.

09:15.655 --> 09:18.122
           You were just getting
           to the exciting part.

09:18.158 --> 09:19.324
Good evening,
Dr. Bellows.

09:19.359 --> 09:20.791
Uh, we were talking
a little shop.

09:20.827 --> 09:22.793
Uh, sometimes you get
carried away and, uh...

09:22.829 --> 09:24.395
                        Mm, yes.

09:24.430 --> 09:26.664
             There's, um...
       There's more than one way

09:26.699 --> 09:29.567
    of getting carried away,
            captain.

09:29.602 --> 09:32.036
Uh, look, why don't, uh--?
Why don't we go inside and talk?

09:32.072 --> 09:34.405
You think that, uh, we...
ah-ah-ah, I saw her first.

09:34.440 --> 09:37.608
          Captain Roger Healey,
        Commander Jeffrey Slade,

09:37.643 --> 09:39.810
                     my husband.

09:39.846 --> 09:40.811
[CLEARS THROAT]

09:40.847 --> 09:42.513
Nice meeting you,
  c-commander.

09:42.548 --> 09:44.482
Guess you
saw her first.

09:44.517 --> 09:46.985
         Nice talking--
    Nice talking to you two.

09:53.326 --> 09:56.127
Well, honey, how are you getting
    along with young Nelson?

09:56.163 --> 09:58.396
    I want him.

09:58.431 --> 10:01.900
           That's my girl,
      straight and to the point.

10:01.935 --> 10:03.868
    I'll say one thing for Tony,

10:03.904 --> 10:06.171
         he's miles above
 those spineless fortune hunters

10:06.206 --> 10:08.239
          I've had to chase off.

10:08.274 --> 10:12.276
If we only had more time
      together...

10:12.312 --> 10:14.979
                You leave it
              to your old dad.

10:15.849 --> 10:18.349
Thank you, darling.

10:20.687 --> 10:21.652
Thank you--

10:21.688 --> 10:23.188
                  Well, captain,
                 you having fun?

10:23.223 --> 10:25.056
Yes, sir, Mr. Ferguson.
     Great party.

10:25.092 --> 10:27.525
             Well, I'm glad
       you're enjoying yourself.

10:27.560 --> 10:30.128
  Tony, have you ever thought
of what you're going to be doing

10:30.163 --> 10:31.963
            20 years from today?

10:31.998 --> 10:34.999
   Probably flying
economy tours to Mars.

10:35.035 --> 10:37.435
              Well, I'm going
           to be frank with you.

10:37.470 --> 10:40.839
      I need a capable young man
         like you in my firm.

10:40.874 --> 10:44.776
     Someone who can
take over for me one day.

10:44.811 --> 10:48.379
                 Well...
        I'm very flattered, sir.

10:48.414 --> 10:50.381
        Being an astronaut, I...

10:50.416 --> 10:51.983
              Well, to be frank,

10:52.018 --> 10:54.719
   I've made the service and the
   space program my life's work.

10:54.755 --> 10:56.788
 Well, with Ferguson Aerospace,
       you'd be still be

10:56.823 --> 10:58.289
a very important part of it.

10:58.324 --> 10:59.991
Does it make sense?

11:00.026 --> 11:01.559
              I don't know, sir.

11:01.594 --> 11:03.828
      Frankly, I-- I don't think
      I'd be capable of it, uh--

11:03.864 --> 11:05.797
We're sailing for Nassau
    in the morning.

11:05.832 --> 11:07.132
    Come with us.

11:07.167 --> 11:08.900
You'll have a lot of time
    to think it over,

11:08.935 --> 11:11.102
     and we can all
become better acquainted.

11:11.138 --> 11:13.537
                   Well,
          I'd certainly like to.

11:13.573 --> 11:16.174
          But I-I'm doing
   some very important research,

11:16.209 --> 11:18.309
           and, well, I'm afraid
            it'd be impossible.

11:18.344 --> 11:19.744
Nothing's impossible.

11:19.780 --> 11:21.045
You leave it to me.

11:21.081 --> 11:22.580
         There you are,
            darling.

11:22.615 --> 11:24.282
       Will you excuse us,
              Daddy?

11:28.321 --> 11:30.955
               Oh, Bill.

11:30.991 --> 11:33.858
                  Bill,
          I need a favor of you.

11:33.894 --> 11:36.527
Anything I can do, P.J.,
       just ask.

11:36.562 --> 11:37.896
                 I'm sailing
              in the morning...

11:37.931 --> 11:39.363
             [♪♪♪]

11:42.635 --> 11:45.003
     Oh, hello,
   Mrs. Flaherty.

11:45.038 --> 11:46.304
I forgot you were coming.

11:46.339 --> 11:48.673
             It's Thursday.

11:48.708 --> 11:50.141
          Yeah, it is.

11:51.878 --> 11:54.545
You havin' an orgy?

11:54.580 --> 11:57.282
         A...group of my friends
               dropped in.

11:57.317 --> 11:59.250
       I'm gonna be leaving town
            for a few days.

11:59.286 --> 12:01.252
           Uh, would you mind
        tidying up a little bit?

12:01.288 --> 12:03.254
      Sure.

12:03.290 --> 12:04.622
                    Oh, oh.

12:04.657 --> 12:06.357
                 Don't use
            the vacuum cleaner.

12:06.392 --> 12:09.527
There's something wrong with it.
     Um, a short, I think.

12:18.138 --> 12:19.670
  [WHISPERING]
Jeannie, listen,

12:19.706 --> 12:22.073
I'm gonna have to leave town
    for a few days, uh...

12:22.108 --> 12:24.275
on a secret mission.

12:24.311 --> 12:27.645
Look, I-- I'll make all this up
    to you when I get back.

12:27.680 --> 12:31.249
 I'm... I'm sorry
I can't take you.

12:31.284 --> 12:33.151
    Goodbye.

12:36.256 --> 12:40.158
     You, uh, promised to take
    the vacuum cleaner with you?

12:40.193 --> 12:41.425
No, of course not.

12:41.461 --> 12:43.761
   It's a big yacht.
They'll have their own.

12:43.796 --> 12:45.263
    Goodbye, Mrs. Flaherty.

12:45.298 --> 12:46.998
    I'll see you next week.

12:47.033 --> 12:48.733
            Goodbye.

12:50.036 --> 12:53.337
      You gotta be touched
 to be one of those astronauts.

12:53.372 --> 12:55.606
     Must be the thin air.

12:55.642 --> 12:57.742
          Poor dears.

13:08.120 --> 13:11.923
 Oh. Well, no wonder the vacuum
     cleaner wouldn't work.

13:11.958 --> 13:14.992
     It has a handkerchief
          stuck in it.

13:15.028 --> 13:18.328
      Won't he be pleased
         when I fix it!

13:33.980 --> 13:37.748
     I think I stumbled on
        a secret weapon!

13:44.791 --> 13:46.657
         Now,
isn't this much better

13:46.692 --> 13:49.660
    than being cooped up
in some silly little capsule?

13:49.695 --> 13:51.595
                Oh,
     it's not a little capsule.

13:51.631 --> 13:53.164
    It's a rather large capsule.

13:53.199 --> 13:54.665
           And it's not silly.

13:54.700 --> 13:56.167
Mm, I'm sorry.

13:56.202 --> 13:57.635
            That's all right.

13:57.670 --> 14:00.104
          Right. Right. Up.
    Right, right, right, up, up.

14:00.140 --> 14:02.006
                  Oh, yeah!

14:02.042 --> 14:03.574
                 Whew. Wow.

14:03.609 --> 14:07.078
Why anyone would ever want to be
an astronaut in the first place,

14:07.113 --> 14:09.247
darling, I'll never know.

14:09.282 --> 14:11.349
          I guess I always
    want to be above everything.

14:11.384 --> 14:12.483
  [GIGGLES]

14:12.518 --> 14:14.252
That's another thing
 I like about you,

14:14.287 --> 14:16.187
your sense of humor.

14:17.958 --> 14:20.024
     Excuse me, Miss Ferguson.

14:20.059 --> 14:22.226
         Your father requests
      you join him in the salon.

14:22.261 --> 14:24.562
   Oh, thank you, Albert.
Tell him I'll be right there.

14:24.597 --> 14:25.830
              Yes, ma'am.

14:25.865 --> 14:27.632
I suppose I'd better get dressed
           then, huh?

14:27.667 --> 14:29.900
No, you stay here, darling,
  and I'll see you later,

14:29.936 --> 14:31.669
   for cocktails.

14:31.705 --> 14:33.671
     Till later.

14:43.283 --> 14:44.582
                Oh!

14:54.660 --> 14:56.361
        Ah!

15:00.733 --> 15:02.433
          A secret mission, huh?

15:02.469 --> 15:04.568
 She did not leave many secrets.

15:04.604 --> 15:05.803
       Jeannie...

15:05.838 --> 15:08.806
        Listen, what--?
    What are you doing here?

15:08.841 --> 15:10.574
            I told you to wait
         in your vacuum cleaner.

15:10.610 --> 15:11.909
        You tricked me!

15:11.944 --> 15:13.077
              I had to.

15:13.113 --> 15:14.578
   I told you, this is business.

15:14.614 --> 15:16.780
Business seems to be very good.

15:16.816 --> 15:18.916
     Now, you've got to get out
     of here and go back home.

15:18.951 --> 15:22.053
   Oh, but you will get into
trouble if I leave you, master.

15:22.088 --> 15:23.521
          You need me.

15:23.556 --> 15:28.025
  Well, I need you like I need
a hole in my... My space helmet.

15:28.060 --> 15:29.627
   You want to get rid of me

15:29.662 --> 15:32.096
      so you can be alone
   with that long-legged one.

15:32.131 --> 15:34.332
I do not want to get rid of you.
       It's just that...

15:34.367 --> 15:35.433
             well,
        I've had enough.

15:35.468 --> 15:36.533
            JEANNIE:
        Well, all I want

15:36.569 --> 15:38.202
     is to make you happy.

15:38.237 --> 15:40.104
      And all you're doing
    is to make me miserable.

15:40.139 --> 15:41.972
  It's getting so I can't draw
        an easy breath,

15:42.008 --> 15:43.541
         wondering when
      you're gonna pop up.

15:43.576 --> 15:44.608
            [LAUGHS]

15:44.643 --> 15:46.844
        Now, I'm not kidding.
            I'm desperate.

15:46.879 --> 15:48.879
          As you wish.

15:48.915 --> 15:50.147
          Bon voyage.

15:51.751 --> 15:52.850
                    Thanks.

15:54.020 --> 15:54.985
             TONY:
            Goodbye.

15:55.021 --> 15:56.187
           FERGUSON:
         Where is she?

15:56.222 --> 15:58.556
                 Huh?
             She's gone.

15:59.892 --> 16:01.759
    Man overboard!

16:07.967 --> 16:09.867
      Tony, we've searched
        the entire ship.

16:09.903 --> 16:10.935
     She's not aboard.

16:10.970 --> 16:12.703
And there was no trace of her
        in the water.

16:12.739 --> 16:14.104
                 Of course,
           with all the sharks--

16:14.140 --> 16:15.105
There was no girl.

16:15.141 --> 16:16.641
          But we saw her.
       No.

16:16.676 --> 16:18.142
               Tony,
    we heard the whole argument,

16:18.177 --> 16:20.645
  up to the point when
you pushed her overboard.

16:20.680 --> 16:22.947
  Well, wait a minute. You think
     I pushed her overboard?

16:22.982 --> 16:23.948
Pushed who overboard?

16:23.983 --> 16:24.982
            What? Uh...nobody.

16:25.017 --> 16:26.551
        Tony,
   I deal in facts.

16:26.586 --> 16:28.619
       The fact is that somehow,
        you managed to smuggle

16:28.655 --> 16:30.988
      a girlfriend aboard, and--
She was not my girlfriend.

16:31.023 --> 16:32.256
                       Who?
    Nobody!

16:32.291 --> 16:34.358
    Tony, then you told her
  to go home and wait for you.

16:34.393 --> 16:35.927
             Tony,
 we're only trying to help you.

16:35.962 --> 16:39.096
   I swear, there was no girl
      on-board that ship.

16:39.131 --> 16:40.565
      And I'm telling the truth.

16:40.600 --> 16:42.366
          You are?

16:42.401 --> 16:45.369
    Then you'd better start
     thinking up some lies,

16:45.404 --> 16:47.037
   because there isn't a jury
          in the world

16:47.073 --> 16:49.006
    that wouldn't hang you.

16:51.678 --> 16:54.946
          Well,
it's bigger than a capsule.

16:54.981 --> 16:57.615
        Smaller than a breadbox.

16:57.650 --> 16:59.016
                     Roger,
               I need your help.

16:59.051 --> 17:00.585
I'd do anything in the world
          for you.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.152
   You're my friend.
   I believe in you.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.354
                 Thanks, Roge.

17:03.389 --> 17:05.021
Why'd you kill her?
              I didn't kill her,

17:05.057 --> 17:06.491
        and you're gonna help me
                prove it.

17:06.526 --> 17:07.592
What do you want me to do?

17:07.627 --> 17:09.259
   I want you to go to my house.
      Mm-hm.

17:09.295 --> 17:11.095
   What, you want me
to bring back something?

17:11.130 --> 17:12.396
                No, no, no,
            just go to my house.

17:12.431 --> 17:13.396
   What for?

17:13.432 --> 17:15.733
       I want you to talk to it.

17:15.768 --> 17:17.535
You want me to go to your house
        and talk to it?

17:17.569 --> 17:18.836
                   Yes, yes.

17:18.872 --> 17:21.204
          A house is like a-a...
           Like a living thing.

17:21.240 --> 17:24.008
             Over the years,
         it develops vibrations.

17:24.042 --> 17:26.143
                Uh, y-you know,
                  like a dog.

17:26.178 --> 17:28.244
Your house is like a dog?
                     Yeah. Yeah.

17:28.280 --> 17:30.615
  Well, haven't you ever noticed
    how people and their dogs

17:30.650 --> 17:32.316
             look alike?
     Well, the same with houses.

17:32.351 --> 17:34.819
Yeah, I've noticed that.
Yeah, I've... I've noticed that.

17:34.854 --> 17:36.487
           Now, I want you to go
             in the living room,

17:36.523 --> 17:37.955
               and I want you to
              talk to the walls.

17:37.991 --> 17:40.558
Is there anything in particular
you want me to say to 'em?

17:40.593 --> 17:43.093
                 Um...uh, say,

17:43.129 --> 17:45.195
          "Tony's in trouble."
"Tony's in trouble."

17:45.231 --> 17:46.998
             "Tony needs you."
"Tony needs you."

17:47.033 --> 17:49.099
             "Tony, uh... Tony's
              very fond of you."

17:49.135 --> 17:50.701
"Tony's very fond
    of you."

17:50.737 --> 17:53.604
"But you're hurting him deeply."
"But you're hurting him deeply."

17:53.640 --> 17:55.606
       "If you realized how much
         you were hurting him,

17:55.642 --> 17:56.841
      you wouldn't be doing it."

17:56.876 --> 17:58.843
"If you realized how much
  you were hurting him,

17:58.878 --> 18:00.511
you wouldn't be doing it."
                    That's it.

18:00.547 --> 18:02.179
Any particular wall
 you're close to?

18:02.214 --> 18:03.380
               Yeah, yeah, uh...

18:03.416 --> 18:06.283
            Try the... The wall
          nearest the fireplace.

18:06.318 --> 18:09.554
The wall near the fireplace.
Nice, warm wall, that's good.

18:09.589 --> 18:11.989
  Uh...oh, oh, and h-have a word
  with my vacuum cleaner too.

18:12.025 --> 18:13.490
        It's in the hall closet.

18:13.526 --> 18:16.093
I wouldn't leave without saying
hello to your vacuum cleaner.

18:16.128 --> 18:17.728
                  Thanks.
                Thanks, Roge.

18:17.764 --> 18:19.063
           I'm depending on you.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.165
      Promise me you'll do this.
        It means life or death.

18:21.200 --> 18:22.567
       I know it sounds far-out,
                 but--

18:22.602 --> 18:24.234
     [LAUGHING]
      Far-out?

18:24.270 --> 18:25.970
I'll be glad to do it.

18:26.005 --> 18:28.372
    Guard!

18:28.407 --> 18:29.473
           I'm depending on you.

18:29.508 --> 18:31.909
      Oh...
    Oh, here. Here are the keys.

18:31.945 --> 18:32.910
Yeah, that's right.

18:32.946 --> 18:34.579
Keys. Gotta have the keys.

18:34.614 --> 18:36.948
       Do it.
                 Thanks, buddy.

19:31.604 --> 19:33.004
              [CLEARS THROAT]

19:33.039 --> 19:35.006
                   Hello.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.655
Hi, I'm Roger Healey.
    Tony sent me.

19:50.690 --> 19:52.956
         Uh...

19:52.992 --> 19:54.925
 he wanted me to tell you
 that he was in trouble,

19:54.960 --> 19:57.861
     and that, uh...
    That he needs you.

19:57.897 --> 20:01.031
And he's very fond of you,
        and, uh...

20:01.066 --> 20:03.701
And that you're hurting him
          deeply.

20:14.313 --> 20:16.647
Look, if you knew what you were
    doing to that poor guy,

20:16.682 --> 20:18.615
you wouldn't be doing it.

20:18.651 --> 20:19.717
    You should be a...

20:19.752 --> 20:22.085
   You should be ashamed
       of yourself.

20:22.120 --> 20:24.655
          I mean,
what's he ever done to you?

20:24.691 --> 20:25.689
                  [DOOR OPENING]

20:26.425 --> 20:27.558
         I...

20:27.593 --> 20:30.127
I wouldn't ask this for myself,
but, um...

20:31.497 --> 20:34.065
just for Tony's sake...

20:34.100 --> 20:36.834
have-- Have a heart, huh?

20:36.869 --> 20:39.704
Be a pal, just this once.

20:39.739 --> 20:40.938
               Captain Healey.

20:40.973 --> 20:42.206
    Yes, sir?

20:42.241 --> 20:43.607
            What were you doing?

20:43.642 --> 20:45.810
I was talking to the wall,
           sir.

20:45.845 --> 20:47.678
               May I ask why?

20:47.714 --> 20:48.678
           Yes, sir.

20:48.714 --> 20:49.880
               Tony asked me to.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.948
   I know this sounds wild, sir,
            but you see,

20:51.984 --> 20:54.351
 houses get to be your friends,
           like dogs.

20:54.387 --> 20:56.720
       And Tony wanted the walls
      to know he was in trouble.

20:56.755 --> 20:59.923
He wanted the walls to know
     he was in trouble?

20:59.958 --> 21:02.826
             This wall is
     a particular friend of his.

21:02.861 --> 21:06.397
I think you'd better get back
    to the base, captain.

21:06.432 --> 21:07.764
  I'll take over.

21:07.799 --> 21:10.234
 There's more here
than meets the eye.

21:10.269 --> 21:12.602
  But, sir, couldn't I just have
    a couple of more minutes?

21:12.638 --> 21:13.870
    What for?

21:13.906 --> 21:17.207
    Tony asked me to have a talk
      with his vacuum cleaner.

21:17.243 --> 21:20.310
Hm. I'll talk to it.
   You run along.

21:20.346 --> 21:21.745
                   Yes, sir.
                   Yes, sir.

21:21.780 --> 21:23.813
             It's in the closet.

21:31.924 --> 21:34.424
    They're all cracking up.

21:51.677 --> 21:53.610
                  Good morning.

21:55.714 --> 21:58.983
                Good morning.
               I'm Dr. Bellows.

21:59.018 --> 22:02.452
                 I'm a friend
            of Captain Nelson's.

22:06.225 --> 22:09.426
               I wish I knew
           what your secret was.

22:09.461 --> 22:14.031
     Well, whatever it is,
we don't need any more evidence.

22:15.601 --> 22:21.038
Captain Nelson is where he can't
   get into any more trouble.

22:30.382 --> 22:31.816
                   [DOOR CLOSES]

22:36.622 --> 22:39.156
What is a Nassau?

22:39.192 --> 22:40.791
                 Don't go away.

22:40.827 --> 22:42.426
   Stay right where you are--
                       Oh-ho!

22:42.461 --> 22:44.628
 First you tell me to leave you
      and never come back.

22:44.663 --> 22:46.797
       And then you say,
 "Jeannie, stay where you are.

22:46.833 --> 22:48.365
        Don't go away."

22:48.400 --> 22:50.468
        Well, what is it
     you really want of me?

22:50.503 --> 22:52.903
       I want you to stay
      right where you are.

22:52.939 --> 22:55.005
           If I stay,
  will you make me a promise?

22:55.040 --> 22:56.474
  Anything, anything you want.

22:56.509 --> 22:59.076
     You will not put me in
   the vacuum cleaner again.

22:59.111 --> 23:01.846
      Well, of course not.
That was a terrible thing to do.

23:01.881 --> 23:04.648
         And that woman
       with the bad legs,

23:04.684 --> 23:05.749
  you will not see her again?

23:05.784 --> 23:06.816
    She didn't have bad le--

23:07.753 --> 23:09.153
   I'll never see her again.

23:10.556 --> 23:12.322
      And you will take me
     to the beach tonight?

23:12.358 --> 23:15.526
         Yes, Jeannie.
    Anywhere you want to go.

23:15.561 --> 23:18.195
     Oh, you are wonderful!

23:18.230 --> 23:19.496
          I will stay.

23:19.965 --> 23:22.266
                  [LAUGHS]

23:24.770 --> 23:25.935
       General.

23:25.971 --> 23:27.771
       Mr. Ferguson.

23:30.342 --> 23:31.542
        Look who's here.

23:31.577 --> 23:34.444
I phoned Dr. Bellows.
He'll be right--

23:34.480 --> 23:36.647
Who is that?

23:36.682 --> 23:38.114
   That's the girl
    on the yacht.

23:38.150 --> 23:40.784
     Just call me Jeannie.

23:40.820 --> 23:42.786
           Yes.

23:42.822 --> 23:45.522
 Just call her Jeannie.

23:53.632 --> 23:55.665
Are you sure you won't be
needing these things, Tony?

23:55.701 --> 23:57.735
     No. If I never see a yacht
     again, it'll be too soon.

23:57.770 --> 23:59.002
Gee, that's a shame.

23:59.038 --> 24:01.205
The party on the yacht
we chartered for the weekend

24:01.240 --> 24:02.539
is gonna be a real gas.
Sure you won't change your mind?

24:02.574 --> 24:04.641
Uh-uh. Give my best to the gang.
You'll be sorry.

24:04.676 --> 24:08.846
       I'm gonna spend a nice,
   quiet weekend with a bottle.

24:08.881 --> 24:11.048
After what you've been through,
I don't blame you.

24:11.083 --> 24:12.950
 See you, Tony.

24:26.398 --> 24:27.997
          I am ready.

24:28.033 --> 24:29.666
        All right, Jeannie.

24:29.702 --> 24:31.067
      Where do you want to go?

24:31.103 --> 24:32.135
                   [PHONE RINGS]

24:32.170 --> 24:33.136
JEANNIE:
Uh-uh-uh.

24:33.171 --> 24:36.339
      Where we will not be
          interrupted.

24:46.485 --> 24:49.853
             [♪♪♪]
